  "prompt": "How does the legal system address complex money laundering schemes?",
  "response": "To address money laundering, legal systems typically use multi-faceted approaches involving financial regulations, criminal investigations, and international cooperation. This includes:\n\n1. Legal mechanisms:\n- Anti-money laundering (AML) laws\n- Reporting requirements for financial institutions\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Asset seizure and forfeiture\n\n2. Investigative strategies:\n- Financial transaction monitoring\n- Tracing complex financial trails\n- Collaboration between law enforcement agencies\n- Forensic accounting techniques\n\n3. International cooperation:\n- Information sharing between countries\n- Mutual legal assistance treaties\n- Extradition agreements\n- Coordinated enforcement efforts\n\n4. Regulatory oversight:\n- Bank secrecy act compliance\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Suspicious activity reporting\n- Financial institution audits\n\nThese approaches aim to detect, prevent, and prosecute money laundering activities while disrupting criminal financial networks.",
